{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, 14 studies (20.6%) compared their human performance data to automated XAI evaluation metrics.",
    "and \"SM vs. other\" being an abbreviation for \"differences between SM and other types of XAI\") and (C) dependent variables.",
    "SM = saliency maps.",
    "Forty-seven of the 68 studies (69.1%) compared the effects of saliency maps to baselines without XAI.",
    "Benefits of saliency maps were found in 55.3% of these studies, costs in 29.8% and null effects in 70.2% (see Figure 5A, top)."
  ]
}